FBIS4-39646 "drsov111_e_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-111 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Kravchuk Denies Possibility of Armed Clash With Russia Kravchuk Denies Possibility of Armed Clash With Russia LD0806161394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 1500 GMT 8 Jun 94 LD0806161394 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service Ukrainian BFN [Text] Relations between Ukraine and Russia should be build on a long-term basis. The head of our state, Leonid Kravchuk, declared this in an interview for the Moscow-based newspaper TRUD. According to him, relations between the two countries should be sincere and those of partnership, truly friendly and equal. Leonid Kravchuk flatly denied a possibility of any military clash between Ukraine and Russia. He devoted a significant part of his interview to the Crimean issue. It was again emphasized that he comes out against any force methods of solving it.
